</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="45" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="45.[108,637,226,812]" pageId="45" pageNumber="45">
DISCUSSION: As in 
<taxonomicName box="[373,537,358,382]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Melaleucaphylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glomeratae">
<emphasis box="[373,397,359,382]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="45">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[417,537,358,382]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="45">glomeratae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schwartz &amp; Weirauch &amp; Schuh" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Melaleucaphylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vimineae">
<emphasis box="[606,630,359,382]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="45">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[108,207,392,415]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="45">vimineae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[207,343,391,415]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="45">
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schwartz &amp; Weirauch &amp; Schuh" authorityYear="2018" box="[221,343,391,415]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Melaleucaphylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ngarkat">M. ngarkat</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has the distal edge of the secondary gonopore with obvious microspiculate lobes but does not have the proximal process of the secondary gonopore as in these two and all other congeners.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
